{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":926,"text":"It would be nice to be\nobjective in life,"},{"time":3571,"text":"in many ways."},{"time":5593,"text":"The problem is that we have\nthese color-tinted glasses"},{"time":8971,"text":"as we look at all kinds of situations."},{"time":13650,"text":"For example, think about\nsomething as simple as beer."},{"time":17366,"text":"If I gave you a few beers to taste"},{"time":19548,"text":"and I asked you to rate them\non intensity and bitterness,"},{"time":23356,"text":"different beers would occupy\ndifferent space."},{"time":27053,"text":"But what if we tried\nto be objective about it?"},{"time":29810,"text":"In the case of beer,\nit would be very simple."},{"time":31970,"text":"What if we did a blind taste?"},{"time":34122,"text":"Well, if we did the same thing,\nyou tasted the same beer,"},{"time":36846,"text":"now in the blind taste,\nthings would look slightly different."},{"time":40817,"text":"Most of the beers will go into one place."},{"time":43039,"text":"You will basically not\nbe able to distinguish them,"},{"time":45484,"text":"and the exception, of course,\nwill be Guinness."},{"time":48573,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":50801,"text":"Similarly, we can think about physiology."},{"time":53587,"text":"What happens when people expect\nsomething from their physiology?"},{"time":56629,"text":"For example, we sold people\npain medications."},{"time":59137,"text":"Some people, we told them\nthe medications were expensive."},{"time":61876,"text":"Some people, we told them it was cheap."},{"time":63757,"text":"And the expensive\npain medication worked better."},{"time":66729,"text":"It relieved more pain from people,"},{"time":69283,"text":"because expectations\ndo change our physiology."},{"time":72787,"text":"And of course, we all know that in sports,"},{"time":74849,"text":"if you are a fan of a particular team,"},{"time":76667,"text":"you can't help but see the game"},{"time":79036,"text":"develop from the perspective of your team."}]},{"cues":[{"time":82541,"text":"So all of those are cases in which\nour preconceived notions"},{"time":86717,"text":"and our expectations color our world."},{"time":90157,"text":"But what happened\nin more important questions?"},{"time":93559,"text":"What happened with questions\nthat had to do with social justice?"},{"time":97111,"text":"So we wanted to think about\nwhat is the blind tasting version"},{"time":100516,"text":"for thinking about inequality?"},{"time":103581,"text":"So we started looking at inequality,"},{"time":105880,"text":"and we did some large-scale surveys"},{"time":107830,"text":"around the U.S. and other countries."},{"time":110384,"text":"So we asked two questions:"},{"time":112335,"text":"Do people know what kind of\nlevel of inequality we have?"},{"time":115701,"text":"And then, what level of inequality\ndo we want to have?"},{"time":119812,"text":"So let's think about the first question."},{"time":122226,"text":"Imagine I took all the people in the U.S."},{"time":124339,"text":"and I sorted them from\nthe poorest on the right"},{"time":127264,"text":"to the richest on the left,"},{"time":129656,"text":"and then I divided them into five buckets:"},{"time":132318,"text":"the poorest 20 percent,\nthe next 20 percent,"},{"time":134616,"text":"the next, the next,\nand the richest 20 percent."},{"time":137472,"text":"And then I asked you to tell me\nhow much wealth do you think"},{"time":140468,"text":"is concentrated in each of those buckets."},{"time":143417,"text":"So to make it simpler,\nimagine I ask you to tell me,"},{"time":145878,"text":"how much wealth do you think\nis concentrated"},{"time":148138,"text":"in the bottom two buckets,"},{"time":150398,"text":"the bottom 40 percent?"},{"time":152659,"text":"Take a second. Think about it\nand have a number."},{"time":155351,"text":"Usually we don't think."},{"time":157255,"text":"Think for a second,\nhave a real number in your mind."},{"time":159740,"text":"You have it?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":161365,"text":"Okay, here's what lots\nof Americans tell us."},{"time":164430,"text":"They think that the bottom 20 percent"},{"time":166357,"text":"has about 2.9 percent of the wealth,"},{"time":168679,"text":"the next group has 6.4,"},{"time":170862,"text":"so together it's slightly more than nine."},{"time":173369,"text":"The next group, they say, has 12 percent,"},{"time":176782,"text":"20 percent,"},{"time":178431,"text":"and the richest 20 percent, people think\nhas 58 percent of the wealth."},{"time":183075,"text":"You can see how this relates\nto what you thought."}]},{"cues":[{"time":186210,"text":"Now, what's reality?"},{"time":187951,"text":"Reality is slightly different."},{"time":189762,"text":"The bottom 20 percent\nhas 0.1 percent of the wealth."},{"time":193575,"text":"The next 20 percent\nhas 0.2 percent of the wealth."},{"time":196826,"text":"Together, it's 0.3."},{"time":198939,"text":"The next group has 3.9,"},{"time":202468,"text":"11.3,"},{"time":204651,"text":"and the richest group\nhas 84-85 percent of the wealth."},{"time":210392,"text":"So what we actually have\nand what we think we have"},{"time":213358,"text":"are very different."}]},{"cues":[{"time":215331,"text":"What about what we want?"},{"time":217421,"text":"How do we even figure this out?"},{"time":219418,"text":"So to look at this,"},{"time":220829,"text":"to look at what we really want,"},{"time":222407,"text":"we thought about\nthe philosopher John Rawls."},{"time":225472,"text":"If you remember John Rawls,"},{"time":227307,"text":"he had this notion\nof what's a just society."},{"time":230557,"text":"He said a just society"},{"time":232039,"text":"is a society that if\nyou knew everything about it,"},{"time":234754,"text":"you would be willing\nto enter it in a random place."},{"time":237187,"text":"And it's a beautiful definition,"},{"time":238711,"text":"because if you're wealthy,\nyou might want the wealthy"},{"time":241189,"text":"to have more money, the poor to have less."},{"time":243226,"text":"If you're poor, you might\nwant more equality."},{"time":245335,"text":"But if you're going\nto go into that society"},{"time":247339,"text":"in every possible situation,\nand you don't know,"},{"time":250659,"text":"you have to consider all the aspects."},{"time":252865,"text":"It's a little bit like blind tasting\nin which you don't know"},{"time":255791,"text":"what the outcome will be\nwhen you make a decision,"},{"time":258461,"text":"and Rawls called this\nthe \"veil of ignorance.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":262176,"text":"So, we took another group,\na large group of Americans,"},{"time":265783,"text":"and we asked them the question\nin the veil of ignorance."},{"time":268538,"text":"What are the characteristics of a country\nthat would make you want to join it,"},{"time":272648,"text":"knowing that you could end\nrandomly at any place?"},{"time":275806,"text":"And here is what we got."},{"time":277285,"text":"What did people want to give\nto the first group,"},{"time":279544,"text":"the bottom 20 percent?"},{"time":281727,"text":"They wanted to give them\nabout 10 percent of the wealth."},{"time":284421,"text":"The next group, 14 percent of the wealth,"},{"time":287021,"text":"21, 22 and 32."}]},{"cues":[{"time":292384,"text":"Now, nobody in our sample\nwanted full equality."},{"time":295890,"text":"Nobody thought that socialism\nis a fantastic idea in our sample."},{"time":300323,"text":"But what does it mean?\n"},{"time":301611,"text":"It means that we have this knowledge gap"},{"time":303649,"text":"between what we have\nand what we think we have,"},{"time":306307,"text":"but we have at least as big a gap\nbetween what we think is right"},{"time":310022,"text":"to what we think we have."}]},{"cues":[{"time":312820,"text":"Now, we can ask these questions,\nby the way, not just about wealth."},{"time":316012,"text":"We can ask it about other things as well."},{"time":318427,"text":"So for example, we asked people\nfrom different parts of the world"},{"time":322630,"text":"about this question,"},{"time":324348,"text":"people who are liberals and conservatives,"},{"time":326691,"text":"and they gave us basically \nthe same answer."},{"time":328735,"text":"We asked rich and poor,\nthey gave us the same answer,"},{"time":331217,"text":"men and women,"},{"time":332518,"text":"NPR listeners and Forbes readers."},{"time":335211,"text":"We asked people in England,\nAustralia, the U.S. --"},{"time":338440,"text":"very similar answers."},{"time":340157,"text":"We even asked different\ndepartments of a university."},{"time":342928,"text":"We went to Harvard and we checked\nalmost every department,"},{"time":345686,"text":"and in fact, from Harvard Business School,"},{"time":347698,"text":"where a few people wanted the wealthy\nto have more and the [poor] to have less,"},{"time":351410,"text":"the similarity was astonishing."},{"time":353950,"text":"I know some of you went\nto Harvard Business School."}]},{"cues":[{"time":356774,"text":"We also asked this question\nabout something else."},{"time":360120,"text":"We asked, what about the ratio\nof CEO pay to unskilled workers?"},{"time":365089,"text":"So you can see what\npeople think is the ratio,"},{"time":368246,"text":"and then we can ask the question,\nwhat do they think should be the ratio?"},{"time":372147,"text":"And then we can ask, what is reality?"},{"time":374774,"text":"What is reality? And you could say,\nwell, it's not that bad, right?"},{"time":378052,"text":"The red and the yellow\nare not that different."},{"time":380205,"text":"But the fact is, it's because\nI didn't draw them on the same scale."},{"time":386105,"text":"It's hard to see, there's yellow\nand blue in there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":390015,"text":"So what about other outcomes of wealth?"},{"time":392360,"text":"Wealth is not just about wealth."},{"time":394055,"text":"We asked, what about things like health?"},{"time":396679,"text":"What about availability\nof prescription medication?"},{"time":400812,"text":"What about life expectancy?"},{"time":402832,"text":"What about life expectancy of infants?"},{"time":405247,"text":"How do we want this to be distributed?"},{"time":407592,"text":"What about education for young people?"},{"time":410401,"text":"And for older people?"},{"time":412271,"text":"And across all of those things,\nwhat we learned was that people"},{"time":415254,"text":"don't like inequality of wealth,"},{"time":418412,"text":"but there's other things where inequality,\nwhich is an outcome of wealth,"},{"time":421918,"text":"is even more aversive to them:"},{"time":423961,"text":"for example, inequality\nin health or education."},{"time":427932,"text":"We also learned that people\nare particularly open"},{"time":430393,"text":"to changes in equality\nwhen it comes to people"},{"time":432947,"text":"who have less agency --"},{"time":434991,"text":"basically, young kids and babies,"},{"time":437336,"text":"because we don't think of them\nas responsible for their situation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":442003,"text":"So what are some lessons from this?"},{"time":444348,"text":"We have two gaps:"},{"time":445508,"text":"We have a knowledge gap\nand we have a desirability gap"},{"time":448088,"text":"And the knowledge gap\nis something that we think about,"},{"time":450710,"text":"how do we educate people?"},{"time":452080,"text":"How do we get people to think\ndifferently about inequality"},{"time":454796,"text":"and the consequences of inequality\nin terms of health, education,"},{"time":458558,"text":"jealousy, crime rate, and so on?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":460949,"text":"Then we have the desirability gap."},{"time":462830,"text":"How do we get people to think differently\nabout what we really want?"},{"time":466653,"text":"You see, the Rawls definition,\nthe Rawls way of looking at the world,"},{"time":470028,"text":"the blind tasting approach,"},{"time":471770,"text":"takes our selfish motivation\nout of the picture."},{"time":474695,"text":"How do we implement that\nto a higher degree"},{"time":477272,"text":"on a more extensive scale?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":479896,"text":"And finally, we also have an action gap."},{"time":482752,"text":"How do we take these things\nand actually do something about it?"},{"time":485701,"text":"I think part of the answer\nis to think about people"},{"time":488603,"text":"like young kids and babies\nthat don't have much agency,"},{"time":491715,"text":"because people seem to be\nmore willing to do this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":495523,"text":"To summarize, I would say,\nnext time you go to drink beer or wine,"},{"time":500793,"text":"first of all, think about, what is it\nin your experience that is real,"},{"time":504880,"text":"and what is it in your experience\nthat is a placebo effect"},{"time":508154,"text":"coming from expectations?"},{"time":509758,"text":"And then think about what it also means\nfor other decisions in your life,"},{"time":513287,"text":"and hopefully also for policy questions\n"},{"time":515362,"text":"that affect all of us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":516667,"text":"Thanks a lot."}]},{"cues":[{"time":518394,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}